Randomize Rows of a Data Frame

Source: R/util.R
randomize_rows.Rd

This function randomly shuffles the rows of a given data frame.

Usage

randomize_rows(data)

Arguments

data

A data frame to be randomized.

Value

A data frame with rows randomly shuffled.

Examples

randomize_rows(mobius_clust_data)
#> # A tibble: 600 × 4
